How to Push a ROS Directory to Github?

Command 1 -> git init
COmmand 2 -> git status (# to check what git is tracking)

Now there are some auto generated files like build log install that are not to be uploaded on github, so have to add those in gitignore

Command 3 -> nano .gitignore
Add these in that file
build/
install/
log/
.vscode/
*.db

If even after adding in gitignore its creating a issue force remove that
Command 4 -> git rm -r --cached -f src/.vscode

Command 5 -> git add .
COmmand 6 -> git commit -m "Initial clean ROS2 project (removed build/install/log/vscode)"

Now will have to link to our github account

Command 7 -> git remote add origin https://github.com/Gautam1704/ros_project.git

My github repo already had README and license so have to link it with my local repo git

Command 8 ->git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
Press ESC
Type :wq
Press Enter

Final Push
Command 9 -> git push -u origin main

If giving error of file size greater the gitignore has not successfully executed forcefully remove something
git rm -r --cached -f src/.vscode
git add .
git commit -m "Removed large files"

Then push
git push -u origin main


